OL,3,CWhat are the Tories, Labour and Lib
OL,4,CDems promising infected blood victims?
OL,6,FOn May 22, Prime Minister Rishi Sunak
OL,7,Fcalled a general election and
OL,8,Fannounced Parliament was to be
OL,9,Fdissolved in a matter of days, putting
OL,10,Finto question the future of the
OL,11,Fcompensation scheme.
OL,13,FThe pledge was tied to a Bill called
OL,14,Fthe Victims and Prisoners Bill, which
OL,15,Fset up a compensation body and pay
OL,16,Finterim payments.
OL,18,FOn May 24, the Bill was one of the
OL,19,Ffinal to pass through Parliament ahead
OL,20,Fof the launch of party campaigns and
OL,21,Fwas given Royal Assent.
