OL,3,CWhat are the Tories, Labour and Lib
OL,4,CDems promising infected blood victims?
OL,6,FMore than 30,000 people were infected
OL,7,Fwith deadly viruses between the 1970s
OL,8,Fand early 1990s as they received blood
OL,9,Ftransfusions or blood products while
OL,10,Freceiving NHS care.
OL,12,FAs a result of the "biggest treatment
OL,13,Fdisaster in NHS history", around 3,000
OL,14,Fpeople have died - among them 380
OL,15,Fchildren - with even more people are
OL,16,Fdying weekly.
